cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with a decentralized networked control system, which involves control theory (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and optimization (cs.MA). The unreliable communication aspect of the system also relates to networking and communication (cs.NI). The use of Riccati recursions and Markov jump linear systems suggests a connection to linear algebra and machine learning (cs.LG).
